11.  what is data binding in angular?\par
Bind binding means the communication between typescript code of the component and template which the uer sees . suppose you have some bussiness logic and you want some  dynamic data from server and wants to render this dynamic data to the tempplate because this is what user sees. this is where data binding comes into picture because we need some sort of communication between typescript code and template .\par
types of data binding\par
1. string interpolation is a one way data binding which is used to output data from typescript code to html template. it uses expression within double curly braces to display data from typescript to template. it evaluates the expression or used to call the methods ex. \{\{expression\}\}\par
2. property bindind is also 1 way data binding which is used to bind the property of the dom elements to the field which is property of typescript code.\par
\tab ex: <h2 [textfield]='title'></h2>\par
here we are binding textfield content of h2 dom element with title which we have defined in component.\par
stringinterpolation and property binding both are 1way binding that means any change in component property , angular will change the dom elements but any change in dom, will not be reflected to components.\par
3. event binding is also one type of binding in angular , which is used to handle event such as button clicked ,mouse moved etc. suppose we have a button in html and we want to handle click event to this button. to implement this we have to bind click event of this button to the method in component.\par
<button (click)='onsave()'>save</button>\par
4. 2way data binding is used when we want to update dom elements and on changing component property and vice versa. 1 way data binding is used to update dom element on changing component property but with the help of 2waydata binding we can achieve feature to update data from component to view and vice versa.\par
<input type ='text' [(ngModel)]='propertyofcomponent'>\par
for two way binding we combine property binding and event binding both, as we call bananna in box syntax\par
